David Klemmer and James Graham could face demerit point penalties or a temporary game ban for their argument with referee Gerard Sutton at the ANZ Stadium on Friday night . 
  Canterbury head of football Todd Greenberg said the match review committee would 'look very closely at' their behaviour . 
  The pair argued with the referee after South Sydney were awarded a penalty in the second half of the game . 
  Canterbury were beaten by South Sydney in the NRL clash . 
  Darren Alchin was taken to hospital with a broken shoulder after spectators threw bottles at officials . 
 